|| Beautiful Unordered List

This project showcases a beautifully styled || unordered list || built using || HTML || CSS and JavaScript. It demonstrates how basic web technologies can be combined to enhance the appearance and interactivity of standard list elements.

|| 🚀 Features

- ✨ Custom styling for unordered lists
- 🎨 Smooth hover and transition effects
- ⚙️ JavaScript-powered interactions (e.g., item toggles, animations, or dynamic list updates)
- 📱 Fully responsive design

 || 📂 Project Structure

```
beautiful-unordered-list/
├── index.html        # Main HTML file
├── styles.css        # Custom CSS styles
├── script.js         # JavaScript for interaction
└── README.md         # Project documentation
```

|| 🛠️ How to Use

1. || Clone this repository || 
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/farhan baber/beautiful-unordered-list.git
   ```

2. || Navigate to the project directory ||
   ```bash
   cd beautiful-unordered-list
   ```

3. || Open `index.html` in your browser ||
   You can simply double-click the file or use a live server in your code editor.

|| 🧪 Customization

- Edit `styles.css` to change colors, fonts, spacing, or add animations.
- Modify `script.js` to add interactivity such as toggling items, removing items, etc.
- Update `index.html` to add or remove list items.


Made with  using HTML, CSS & JavaScript.
